%U A394898 -3,0,0,1,1,1,7,1,0,7,0,1,21,1,0,-1,-2,-2,-4,-4,0,1,3,15,1,0,9,0,1,1,3,9,1,0,0,-1,0,0
%N A394898 Irregular triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = A027750(n,k) - 2*A027750(n,k-1) with 2 <= k <= A000005(n) and T(n,1) = 1.
%C A394898 The sum of row n equals A033879(n), the deficiency of n.
%C A394898 The number of positive terms in row n equals A237271(n), the number of 2-dense sublists of divisors of n.
%C A394898 If T(n,k) is a positive integer then the k-th divisor of n is also the smallest and the first number in one of the 2-dense sublists of divisors of n and also it is a member of the n-th row of the triangle A379288.
%C A394898 n is a 2-dense number (A174973) if and only if the only positive integer in row n is the initial 1.
%C A394898 n is a number with two or more 2-dense sublists of divisors (A238524) if and only if the row n contains two or more positive integers.
%C A394898 n is odd if and only if the row n ends in an odd number (A005408).
%C A394898 n is even if and only if the row n ends in 0.
%C A394898 n is a prime number (A000040) if and only if the row n has two terms.
%C A394898 n is an odd prime (A065091) if and only if the row n lists [1, n - 2].
%C A394898 n is a square (A000290) if and only if the length of the row n is odd.
%C A394898 n is a number whose deficiency is 2 (A191363) if and only if the row n lists 1 together with (A000005(n) - 2)/2 zeros followed by 1 together with (A000005(n) - 2)/2 zeros.
%C A394898 n is a power of 2 (A000079) if and only if the row n lists 1 together with A032741(n) zeros. These numbers have deficiency 1.
%C A394898 n is an even perfect number (cf. A000396) if and only if the row n lists 1 together with (A000005(n) - 2)/2 zeros followed by -1 together with (A000005(n) - 2)/2 zeros. These numbers have deficiency 0.
%C A394898 It is not known whether the sum of row n can be -1. In other words: it is not known whether there are numbers with deficiency -1. See comments in A033879 and A033880.
%H A394898 Antti Karttunen, <a href="/A394898/b394898.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..15937; the first 2048 rows of the triangle</a>
%e A394898 Triangle begins:
%e A394898   ------------------------------------
%e A394898    n\k  1   2   3   4   5   6   7   8
%e A394898   ------------------------------------
%e A394898    1 |  1;
